sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as Frontend<br/>(Next.js)
    participant API as Server API<br/>(FastAPI)
    participant Agent as Multi-Agent<br/>System (Server)
    participant Core as Core Models<br/>(starboard-core)
    participant Tools as Tools<br/>(Server)
    participant LogParser as Log Parser<br/>(starboard-log-parser)
    participant DB as Databricks<br/>API
    
    User->>Frontend: "Analyze job 123"
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/chat/messages
    
    Note over API: Route to multi-agent system
    
    API->>Agent: handle_message()
    Agent->>Core: Load Message model
    Core-->>Agent: Message instance
    
    Agent->>Agent: Route to JobAgent
    Agent->>Tools: execute resolve_job("123")
    Tools->>DB: GET /api/2.0/jobs/get?job_id=123
    DB-->>Tools: Job metadata
    
    Note over Tools: Need to parse event logs
    
    Tools->>DB: Get log path
    DB-->>Tools: dbfs:/cluster-logs/eventlog.gz
    
    Tools->>LogParser: create_spark_application(path)
    LogParser->>DB: Read log from DBFS
    DB-->>LogParser: Event log data
    LogParser->>LogParser: Parse events
    LogParser-->>Tools: SparkApplication
    
    Tools->>Tools: Extract metrics from SparkApplication
    Tools-->>Agent: {job_data, metrics, ...}
    
    Agent->>Core: Create Episode (working memory)
    Core-->>Agent: Episode instance
    
    Agent->>Agent: Generate recommendations
    Agent->>Core: Create output Message
    Core-->>Agent: Message instance
    
    Agent-->>API: FinalOutputEvent
    API-->>Frontend: SSE: final_output
    Frontend-->>User: Display recommendations
    
    Note over API: Persist conversation
    
    API->>Core: Conversation model
    Core-->>API: Immutable Conversation
    API->>API: Save to database

